A new bill is expected to be announced giving the Government powers to replace parts of the protocol unilaterally. Former Brexit advisor to Theresa May, Raoul Ruparel said: "There’s clearly a sense within this current Government that a strategy of setting out a hard line — what some people have called ‘mad-man strategy’ — has worked before and would work again in forcing some kind of move from the EU side." Talks between the UK and the EU have made little progress despite months of negotiations but will resume on Thursday with one UK official warning the UK may have "no choice" but to "do what we can to protect the Belfast/Good Friday Agreement". FOLLOW BELOW FOR LIVE UPDATES...